ard%20was%20maxed%20out%20and%20had%20been%20for%20years%3B%20I%20could%20barely%20afford%20to%20make%20the%20minimum%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20supposed%20to%20be%20like%20this.%20I%20had%20gotten%20my%20master's%20degree%2C%20won%20a%20Fulbright%20scholarship%20and%20worked%20on%20Capitol%20Hill.%20I'd%20just%20wrapped%20up%20an%20internship%20at%20Chase%20Bank.%20Yet%2C%20here%20I%20was%2C%20a%20broke%20twenty-something%20who%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20get%20her%20bags%20on%20an%20airplane.%20How%20could%20I%20expect%20to%20start%20a%20career%20managing%20other%20people's%20money%20if%20I%20couldn't%20even%20manage%20my%20own%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20broke%20down%2C%20the%20ticketing%20agent%20sighed%2C%20eyeing%20the%20long%20line%20of%20passengers%20behind%20me.%20He%20waved%20his%20hand%2C%20%26quot%3BJust%20go.%26quot%3B%20I%20felt%20like%20the%20world's%20biggest%20failure%20as%20I%20boarded%20my%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnderstanding%20I%20wasn't%20alone%20helped%20me%20change%20my%20spending%20habits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20always%20been%20a%20spender%20and%20often%20lived%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20later%2C%20I%20was%20settling%20into%20a%20career%20in%20asset%20management%20at%20J.P.%20Morgan.%20I%20still%20had%20a%20ton%20of%20debt%20and%20bloated%20expenses.%20Rent%2C%20student%20loans%2C%20saving%20for%20a%20wedding%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0everything%20was%20a%20priority%20except%20for%20my%20future.%20I%20was%20barely%20contributing%20to%20my%20retirement%20savings.%20Mainly%20because%20I%20was%20in%20my%2020s%20and%20retirement%20felt%20distant%2C%20but%20also%20because%20of%20my%20poor%20spending%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20always%20something%20tempting%20to%20spend%20on.%20And%20I'm%20not%20alone.%20Saving%20money%20is%20hard%20for%20many%20people%20at%20all%20income%20levels.%20This%20became%20more%20apparent%20the%20longer%20I%20worked%20in%20retirement%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20J.P.%20Morgan%2C%20I%20was%20asked%20to%20design%20a%20brand-new%20product%3A%20a%20suite%20of%20Target%20Date%20Funds.%20The%20development%20process%20involved%20lots%20of%20data-driven%20research%20about%20how%20Americans%20save%20for%20retirement%20and%20why%20our%20brains%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20implementing%20our%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20just%20like%20everyone%20else%20struggling%20to%20resist%20temptation%2C%20it%20became%20easier%20to%20shift%20my%20habits.%20I%20went%20from%20believing%20I%20was%20a%20failure%20because%20I%20couldn't%20save%20to%20developing%20a%20set%20of%20rules%20for%20myself%20that%20made%20saving%20automatic%20and%20removed%20most%20financial%20temptations%20from%20my%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaving%20money%20is%20hard%2C%20and%20technology%20is%20making%20it%20harder%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20working%20for%20almost%20three%20decades%20as%20a%20portfolio%20manager%20and%2015%20years%20of%20applying%20everything%20I%20learned%20about%20behavioral%20economics%20and%20building%20retirement%20funds%20to%20my%20own%20life%2C%20I%20still%20find%20it%20hard%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20does%20get%20easier%20with%20practice%2C%20but%20I%20still%20rely%20on%20many%20of%20the%20rules%20I%20developed%2C%20like%20making%20sure%20I%20never%20go%20shopping%20without%20a%20list%2C%20to%20manage%20my%20spending%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETargeted%20ads%20and%20deals%20in%20your%20inbox%20mean%20every%20Google%20search%20stalks%20you%20perpetually.%20But%20technology%20has%20also%20made%20saving%20more%20difficult%20in%20less%20obvious%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDigital%20payment%20has%20removed%20a%20lot%20of%20friction%20from%20the%20act%20of%20spending%20money.%20Buying%20things%20now%20is%20almost%20completely%20frictionless.%20You%20don't%20even%20have%20to%20open%20your%20wallet%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0just%20tap%20your%20phone%20or%20Apple%20watch%2C%20and%20money%20disappears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFifty%20years%20ago%2C%20if%20you%20wanted%20to%20buy%20something%2C%20you%20had%20to%20physically%20go%20to%20the%20store%20and%20pay%20with%20cash%20or%20write%20a%20check.%20There%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20between%20the%20decision%20to%20buy%20something%20and%20the%20act%20of%20buying%20it%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20friction%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20one%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20save%20is%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20slow%20down%20your%20spending%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0create%20friction%20for%20yourself.%20Here%20are%20some%20strategies%20I've%20developed%20that%20can%20help%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20a%20spending%20plan.%20Be%20brutally%20honest%20with%20how%20much%20you%20can%20afford%20to%20spend%20every%20day%2Fweek%2Fmonth%20and%20keep%20track.%20If%20you%20spend%20too%20much%20one%20day%2Fweek%2Fmonth%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20cut%20back%20the%20next%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EPay%20in%20cash.%20The%20idea%20that%20paying%20for%20things%20can%20cause%20varying%20pain%20levels%20was%20pioneered%20by%20a%20Ph.D.%20student%20at%20Carnegie%20Mellon%2C%20Ofer%20Zellermayer%2C%20in%20the%201990s.%20Research%20has%20shown%20that%20paying%20cash%20for%20things%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmu.edu%2Fhomepage%2Fpractical%2F2007%2Fwinter%2Fspending-til-it-hurts.shtml%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%2522Credit%2520cards%2520effectively%2Chand%2520over%2520bills.%2522%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20painful%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20more%20uncomfortable%20the%20process%20is%2C%20the%20less%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20buy%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EWrite%20checks.%20It%20will%20make%20you%20feel%20like%20everyone%20in%20line%20behind%20you%20is%20staring%20at%20you%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20they%20probably%20are.%20Any%20time%20you%20make%20an%20experience%20painful%2C%20you%20will%20avoid%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20lists.%20Don't%20let%20yourself%20go%20into%20a%20store%20or%20visit%20a%20shop's%20website%20unless%20you%20have%20something%20specific%20you%20want%20to%20buy.%20If%20it%20isn't%20on%20your%20list%2C%20it%20doesn't%20go%20into%20your%20shopping%20cart.%20That%20same%20advice%20goes%20for%20trying%20things%20on%2C%20too%2C%20if%20you%20like%20clothes.%20Once%20you%20see%20how%20well%20something%20fits%20and%20how%20great%20it%20looks%2C%20you%20are%20far%20more%20likely%20to%20buy%20it.%20The%20best%20way%20to%20avoid%20temptation%3F%20Don't%20go%20there!%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESet%20aside%20a%20specific%20time%2C%20say%20once%20a%20week%2C%20and%20a%20specific%20place%2C%20like%20your%20kitchen%20table%2C%20for%20online%20shopping.%20You%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20feel%20pressure%20to%20buy%20or%20to%20buy%20emotionally%20when%20you%20are%20being%20methodical%20about%20your%20purchases%2C%20from%20having%20a%20list%20to%20only%20allowing%20yourself%20to%20purchase%20at%20a%20specific%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAvoid%20%26quot%3Bauto-renew%26quot%3B%20whenever%20you%20can.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crresearch.com%2Fblog%2Fsubscription-service-statistics-and-costs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20%3C%2Fa%3Edone%20by%20C%2BR%20Research%20in%202022%2C%20the%20average%20American%20has%20over%20%24219%20in%20monthly%20subscriptions.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20the%20study's%20participants%20said%20they%20had%20forgotten%20about%20a%20subscription%20and%20were%20paying%20for%20something%20they%20no%20longer%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20kind%20to%20yourself%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20aren't%20consistently%20hitting%20your%20savings%20goals.%20See%20if%20you%20can%20figure%20out%20if%20something%20is%20consistently%20derailing%20you%20and%20view%20each%20slip%20as%20a%20chance%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20yourself.%20Building%20up%20your%20savings%20and%20your%20savings%20muscles%20i