rates%20up%20or%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20mortgage%20rates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-does-fed-impact-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3Earen't%20directly%20tied%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20do%20tend%20to%20fluctuate%20depending%20on%20how%20investors%20believe%20Fed%20moves%20will%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%20Because%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20expected%20to%20keep%20its%20benchmark%20rate%20high%20for%20at%20least%20a%20few%20more%20months%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-mortgage-interest-rate%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20expected%20to%20remain%20elevated%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20may%20get%20an%20idea%20of%20when%20to%20expect%20a%20rate%20cut%20during%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell's%20post-meeting%20press%20conference.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20Fed's%20stance%20has%20been%20that%20it%20will%20likely%20start%20cutting%20rates%20at%20some%20point%20this%20year%2C%20but%20it%20wants%20to%20see%20more%20data%20showing%20that%20inflation%20is%20continuing%20to%20come%20down%20before%20it%20does%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20is%20still%20the%20Fed's%20stance%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20may%20stay%20near%20their%20current%20levels%20or%20inch%20down%20a%20bit.%20But%20if%20Powell%20hints%20that%20we%20may%20need%20to%20wait%20longer%20than%20initially%20expected%20for%20a%20rate%20cut%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20could%20increase%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMortgage%20Rates%20Today%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%3EMortgage%20Refinance%20Rates%20Today%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EMortgage%20Calculator%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EUse%20our%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2240%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgage-calculator%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20mortgage%20calculator%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20see%20how%20today's%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20affect%20your%20monthly%20and%20long-term%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20plugging%20in%20different%20term%20lengths%20and%20interest%20rates%2C%20you'll%20see%20how%20your%20monthly%20payment%20could%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E30-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%2030-year%20fixed%20mortgage%20rate%20was%206.74%25%20last%20week%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fpmms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFreddie%20Mac%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%2014%20basis%20points%20lower%20than%20it%20was%20the%20week%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20is%20the%20most%20common%20type%20of%20home%20loan.%20With%20this%20type%20of%20mortgage%2C%20you'll%20pay%20back%20what%20you%20borrowed%20over%2030%20years%2C%20and%20your%20interest%20rate%20won't%20change%20for%20the%20life%20of%20the%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lengthy%2030-year%20term%20allows%20you%20to%20spread%20out%20your%20payments%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20meaning%20you%20can%20keep%20your%20monthly%20payments%20lower%20and%20more%20manageable.%20The%20trade-off%20is%20that%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20you%20would%20with%20shorter%20terms%20or%20adjustable%20rates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E15-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%206.16%25%20last%20week%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%20data%2C%20which%20is%20a%20six-basis-point%20decrease%20from%20the%20previous%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20m