nsumer%20confidence%20survey%20suggests%20people%20have%20increasingly%20been%20scrapping%20plans%20to%20buy%20homes%20and%20cars.%20Given%20the%20economic%20challenges%2C%20that's%20not%20surprising.%20She%20added%20that%20consumers%20expect%20inflation%20and%20interest%20rates%20to%20come%20down%2C%20meaning%20that%20many%20may%20hold%20off%20on%20some%20big%20purchases%20until%20things%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20rational%20consumer%2C%20you'll%20say%20to%20yourself%2C%20'Well%2C%20maybe%20I'll%20just%20wait%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20not%20everyone%20is%20in%20a%20position%20to%20wait.%20It's%20one%20thing%20if%20you%20want%20to%20buy%20a%20new%20car%20because%20you're%20bored%20with%20the%20old%20one%2C%20but%20it's%20another%20thing%20if%20your%20car%20breaks%20down%20and%20you%20can't%20get%20to%20work.%20Regardless%2C%20waiting%20isn't%20particularly%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20work%2C%20the%20vibe%20is%20static%2C%20too.%20Yes%2C%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20strong%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjanuary-jobs-report-labor-market-good-economy-inflation-wages-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit's%20not%20a%20great%20time%20to%20go%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Companies%20aren't%20laying%20people%20off%20en%20masse%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20not%20bringing%20employees%20on%20board%20quickly.%20Hiring%20has%20slowed%20significantly%20from%20where%20it%20was%20in%202021%20and%202022.%20And%2C%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FEconBerger%2Fstatus%2F1765396629148877238%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emuch%20lower%20than%20one%20would%20expect%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20current%20unemployment%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20are%20hiring%20as%20if%20there's%20a%20relatively%20weak%20labor%20market%2C%20not%20a%20strong%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matt%20Darling%2C%20a%20senior%20employment-policy%20analyst%20at%20the%20Niskanen%20Center%2C%20a%20center-right%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20downshift%20in%20hiring%20has%20also%20tipped%20the%20balance%20of%20power%20back%20toward%20employers.%20While%20wages%20are%20still%20on%20the%20upswing%2C%20switching%20jobs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnick_bunker%2Fstatus%2F1767996338300465656%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emay%20not%20come%20with%20as%20much%20of%20a%20pay%20bump%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20did%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-still-going-layoffs-low-job-openings-quits-high-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreat%20Resignation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202021%20and%202022.%20That%20may%20be%20fine%20for%20those%20who%20are%20happy%20in%20their%20jobs%2C%20which%20many%20people%20are%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20so%20great%20for%20those%20who%20are%20feeling%20a%20little%20antsy%20or%20underappreciated.%20And%20for%20those%20Americans%20who%20find%20themselves%20out%20of%20work%20and%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20gig%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20minute.%20Darling%20told%20me%20that%20for%20the%20unemployed%2C%20it%20takes%20about%20twice%20as%20long%20to%20get%20a%20job%20as%20it%20did%20before%202008.%20A%20job%20search%20that%20used%20to%20take%2010%20weeks%20at%20a%20similar%20unemployment%20rate%20now%20takes%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20obviously%20a%20huge%20source%20of%20dissatisfaction%2C%20because%2020%20weeks%20is%20a%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Darling%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20that%2C%20five%20months%20to%20be%20looking%20for%20a%20job%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20this%20all%20translates%20to%20is%20a%20scenario%20where%20some%20Americans%20feel%20trapped.%20They%20can%20put%20food%20on%20the%20table%20and%20fill%20up%20their%20gas%20tanks%2C%20albeit%20at%20a%20price%20they'd%20rather%20not%20be%20paying.%20But%20it's%20hard%20and%20expensive%20to%20move%20up%20the%20ladder%20in%20many%20meaningful%20ways.%20In%20a%20consumerist%20society%20that%20encourages%20people%20to%20want%20more%20and%20a%20culture%20that%20prizes%20itself%20on%20economic%20mobility%2C%20this%20level%20of%20stillness%20is%20uncomfortable.%20While%20it's%20still%20possible%20to%20get%20a%20better%20job%20or%20a%20new%20house%2C%20those%20things%20feel%20like%20they're%20off%20in%20some%20nebulous%20future%2C%20out%20of%20your%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETamara%20Charm%2C%20a%20partner%20in%20consumer%20insights%20at%20McKinsey%2C%20told%20me%20that%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20shifting%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction%20and%20downgrading%20where%20they%20can%3B%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20some%20people%20are%20switching%20to%20private%20labels%20and%20generic%20brands%20to%20save%20money.%20She%20added%20that%20while%20people%20feel%20boxed%20out%20of%20big-ticket%20goods%2C%20they're%20still%20spending%20on%20treats%20%E2%80%94%20on%20vacations%2C%20on%20cosmetics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we've%20seen%20is%20that%20consumers%20are%20both%20wanting%20to%20trade%20down%2C%20given%20all%20these%20economic%20concerns%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%20they%20want%20to%20splurge%2C%26quot%3B%20Charm%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can't%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20you%20may%20as%20well%20get%20that%20plane%20ticket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fus-consumer-sentiment-holds-steady-in-march-inflation-expectations-remain-above-fed-s-2-target-1033168397%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20bullish%20about%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20they%20were%20six%20months%20ago%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20as%20satisfied%20as%20they%20were%20in%2C%20say%2C%202019%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20clear%20if%20they%20ever%20will%20be.%20It's%20impossible%20to%20predict%20what's%20ahead%2C%20and%20while%20t