%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20American%20Immigration%20Lawyers%20Association%20(AILA)%20has%20written%20to%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20urging%20continued%20immigration%20reforms.%20They%20emphasize%20the%20need%20to%20address%20immigrant%20visa%20backlogs%2C%20expand%20visa%20renewal%20programs%2C%20modernize%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20program%2C%20revise%20shortage%20occupation%20lists%2C%20and%20renew%20regulations%20for%20timely%20work%20authorization.%20These%20recommendations%20aim%20to%20alleviate%20hardships%20faced%20by%20immigrants%20and%20promote%20economic%20and%20social%20well-being%20in%20the%20United%20States.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Lubna%20Kably%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fkey-us-immigration-reform-recommendations-made-by-aila%2Farticleshow%2F108644193.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fkey-us-immigration-reform-recommendations-made-by-aila%2Famp_articleshow%2F108644193.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fkey-us-immigration-reform-recommendations-made-by-aila%2Famp_articleshow%2F108644193.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Allahabad%20HC%20Expunges%20Bareilly%20Judge's%20Remarks%20Hailing%20Adityanath%2C%20Blaming%20Muslims%20for%20Riots%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08101344%2FFcWENqHaQAIDJ0v.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20has%20expunged%20the%20controversial%20observations%20made%20by%20a%20judge%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Bareilly%20who%20had%20recently%20hailed%20chief%20minister%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20as%20a%20modern-day%20%E2%80%98philosopher%20king%E2%80%99%20and%20blamed%20Muslims%20for%20communal%20riots%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20said%20the%20remarks%20made%20by%20additional%20district%20judge-fast%20track%20court%20Ravi%20Kumar%20Diwakar%20on%20March%205%20were%20%E2%80%9Cunwarranted%20expressions%20containing%20political%20over-tones%20and%20personal%20views%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20remarks%20in%20a%20case%20related%20to%20the%20Bareilly%20riots%20of%202010%20drew%20severe%20criticism%2C%20with%20activists%20and%20lawyers%20groups%20demanding%20action%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2019%2C%20while%20hearing%20a%20criminal%20revision%20petition%20filed%20by%20Muslim%20cleric%20Maulana%20Tauqeer%20Raza%20Khan%2C%20whom%20judge%20Diwakar%20had%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmain%20mastermind%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Bareilly%20riots%2C%20the%20high%20court%20also%20pulled%20up%20the%20lower%20court%20judge%20for%20sharing%20his%20personal%20experiences%20in%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Ram%20Manohar%20Narayan%20Mishra%20said%20this%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20at%20all%20required%20while%20passing%20passing%20judicial%20order%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Mishra%20noted%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20expected%20from%20the%20judicial%20officer%20to%20express%20or%20depict%20his%20personal%20or%20pre%20conceived%20notions%20or%20inclinations%20in%20the%20matter.%20The%20judicial%20order%20is%20meant%20for%20public%20consumption%20and%20such%20type%20of%20order%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20misconstrued%20by%20the%20masses.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Mishra%20further%20said%20that%20it%20was%20expected%20from%20the%20judicial%20officer%20that%20%E2%80%9Che%20should%20use%20a%20very%20guarded%20expression%20while%20focusing%20upon%20the%20issue%20in%20hand%20and%20should%20not%20use%20any%20observation%20which%20are%20tangent%20or%20alien%20to%20the%20core%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20expunged%20the%20portion%20from%20the%20last%20paragraph%20of%20page%20six%20to%20the%20middle%20part%20of%20page%208%20of%20the%20March%205%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Diwakar%20on%20March%205%20%E2%80%93%20while%20invoking%20serious%20criminal%20charges%20including%20attempt%20to%20murder%20against%20prominent%20Muslim%20cleric-politician%20Maulana%20Khan%20for%20communal%20violence%20in%20Bareilly%20in%202010%20%E2%80%93%20hailed%20Adityanath%20as%20a%20great%20example%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Creligious%20person%E2%80%9D%20holding%20seat%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20order%2C%20judge%20Diwakar%2C%20who%20had%20earlier%20served%20in%20Varanasi%20and%20passed%20controversial%20orders%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20matter%2C%20made%20a%20string%20of%20seemingly%20controversial%20and%20prejudiced%20observations.%20Not%20only%20did%20he%20lavish%20Adityanath%20with%20praise%20for%20his%20religious%20background%20but%20he%20also%20blamed%20the%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cappeasement%E2%80%9D%20of%20a%20particular%20community%20(Muslims)%20by%20political%20parties%20for%20riots%20in%20the%20country%20and%20reflected%20on%20his%20own%20record%20as%20a%20judge%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20legal%20battle%20and%20claimed%20that%20he%20and%20his%20family%20were%20living%20under%20fear%20after%20receiving%20threats%20from%20Muslim%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiwakar%20described%20Adityanath%20as%20a%20modern-day%20example%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98philosopher%20king%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20concept%20of%20theocratic%20ruler%20propounded%20by%20ancient%20Greek%20philosopher%20Plato%20in%20his%20work%20Republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Diwakar%20further%20remarked%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmain%20reason%20for%20riots%E2%80%9D%20in%20India%20was%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20parties%20here%20are%20engaged%20in%20appeasement%20of%20a%20particular%20religion.%E2%80%9D%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20the%20morale%20of%20prominent%20people%20of%20that%20%E2%80%9Cparticular%20religion%E2%80%9D%20increases%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20believe%20that%20even%20if%20they%20cause%20riots%2C%20no%20harm%20will%20fall%20upon%20them%20due%20to%20protection%20provided%20by%20power%2C%20said%20Diwakar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20hearing%20the%202010%20Bareilly%20riots%20case%2C%20judge%20Diwakar%20added%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20name%20in%20the%20chargesheet%20and%20summoned%20him%20to%20appear%20before%20it%20on%20March%2011.%20Khan%20is%20a%20prominent%20cleric%20of%20the%20Barelvi%20sect%20and%20president%20of%20the%20political%20party%20Ittehad-e-Millat%20Council.%20The%20judge%20dubbed%20Khan%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmain%20mastermind%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20riots%20that%20took%20place%20in%20Bareilly%20on%20March%202%2C%202010%20during%20after%20a%20dispute%20broke%20out%20over%20the%20route%20of%20a%20Muslim%20religious%20procession.%20Several%20persons%20were%20injured%20and%20property%20damaged%20in%20the%20incident.%20A%20curfew%20had%20been%20imposed%20in%20the%20city%20for%20several%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20serving%20as%20a%20judge%20in%20Varanasi%20in%202022%2C%20Diwakar%20had%20passed%20controversial%20directions%20regarding%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid.%20Diwakar%2C%20as%20civil%20judge%20senior%20division%2C%20had%20ordered%20the%20sealing%20of%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20Mughal-era%20mosque%20after%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20claimed%20that%20a%20stone%20found%20in%20the%20ablution%20tank%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cshivling%E2%80%9D.%20Judge%20Diwakar%20had%20given%20his%20nod%20to%20the%20videography%20inside%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20by%20a%20court-appointed%20advocate%20commissioner%20on%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20five%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20demanding%20daily%20access%20to%20prayer%20to%20an%20alleged%20Hindu%20side%20Maa%20Shringar%20Gauri%20they%20claimed%20was%20located%20outside%20the%20western%20wall%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710926442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08101344%2FFcWENqHaQAIDJ0v.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2