streams%2C%20compared%20with%2027%25%20for%20TV%20shows%2C%20and%2018%25%20for%20movies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Deloitte%2018th%20annual%20Digital%20Media%20Trends%20Survey%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fa1cdf4af076d3cf91d4d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22808%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDeloitte%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20when%20they%20do%20turn%20on%20streaming%20services%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20more%20likely%20than%20not%20to%20watch%20something%20based%20on%20social-media%20creators'%20recommendations%2C%20not%20the%20streamer's%20algorithm%2C%20Deloitte%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sobering%20findings%20come%20from%20Deloitte's%2018th%20annual%20Digital%20Media%20Trends%20Survey%2C%20which%20was%20published%20on%20March%2020.%20The%20online%20survey%20of%203%2C517%20online%20consumers%20was%20conducted%20online%20in%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20findings%20suggest%20a%20brighter%20future%20for%20YouTube%20than%20for%20Netflix%20and%20other%20streamers%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-not-netflix-is-big-threat-to-hollywood-analysis-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20we've%20previously%20examined).%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20surprise%20Gen%20Z%20prefers%20social%20media%2C%20given%20it's%20the%20first%20cohort%20to%20be%20raised%20on%20it.%20Those%20preferences%20could%20change%20as%20Gen%20Z%20ages%2C%20but%20that%20would%20mean%20changing%20not%20just%20what%20they%20watch%2C%20but%20what%20they%20watch%20it%20on.%20Other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F90929341%2Folder-millennials-vs-gen-z-streaming-tv-likes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20suggested%20that%20the%20device%20people%20grew%20up%20on%20is%20the%20one%20they%20end%20up%20preferring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20grew%20up%20with%20scr