C%20and%20Ramgarh%2C%20locals%20are%20preoccupied%20with%20land%3A%20its%20loss%20to%20mining%2C%20their%20fight%20to%20retain%20it%2C%20and%20their%20dream%20to%20regain%20it.%20Those%20living%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20coal-mining%20sector%20say%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20trust%20jobs%20as%20only%20a%20few%20of%20them%20are%20formally%20or%20consistently%20engaged%20with%20the%20coal%20economy.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20keeps%20them%20focused%20on%20issues%20of%20land%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahuatand%2C%20a%20Santhal%20village%20in%20Ramgarh%20district%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20is%20an%20example%20of%20what%20the%20closure%20of%20coal%20mining%20can%20set%20off%20in%20rural%20communities%20around%20mines.%20With%20the%20first%20energy%20transition%E2%80%94when%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funacademy.com%2Fcontent%2Fupsc%2Fstudy-material%2Fpublic-administration%2Fpublic-sector-undertakings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20sector%20undertaking%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(PSU)%20set%20up%20its%20mine%20in%20the%201980s%E2%80%94residents%20lost%20their%20agricultural%20land%20and%2C%20hence%2C%20their%20generational%20wealth%20and%20food%20security.%20They%20became%20almost%20entirely%20dependent%20on%20the%20coal%20job%20economy.%20The%20jobs%20are%20few.%20While%20the%20handful%20of%20employees%20still%20continue%20to%20receive%20their%20salary%2C%20this%20source%20may%20soon%20run%20its%20course%20as%20the%20mine%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Franchi%2F8-coal-mines-shut-in-ramgarh-for-over-a-year-production-loss-pegged-at-12l-metric-tonnes-daily%2Farticleshow%2F86948950.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBablu%20Hembrom%2C%20who%20fought%20for%20a%20job%20with%20the%20mining%20company%20and%20finally%20secured%20it%20in%202016%2C%20goes%20in%20daily%20to%20mark%20his%20attendance.%20Father%20of%20two%2C%20Bablu%20knows%20the%20future%20is%20uncertain%20for%20the%20younger%20residents%20of%20the%20remote%20village.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20us%20regret%20the%20decision%20our%20parents%20or%20grandparents%20took%20in%201964%20to%20swap%20agricultural%20land%20for%20compensation%20or%20jobs.%20Coal%20mining%20started%20in%201984.%20The%20money%20we%20received%20as%20compensation%20has%20run%20out%20for%20many%20of%20us.%20Jobs%20came%20to%20only%20one%20person%20in%20each%20family.%20That%20will%20also%20not%20last.%20In%20the%20future%2C%20we%20will%20end%20up%20as%20beggars%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20According%20to%20Sarpanch%20Kiran%20Devi%2C%20approximately%2075%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20here%20is%20unemployed.%20%E2%80%9CWorking-age%20adults%2C%20even%20when%20they%20have%20education%20and%20degrees%2C%20are%20financially%20dependent%20on%20their%20parents.%E2%80%9D%20Biju%20Oraon%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20other%20industries%20develop%2C%20will%20there%20be%20enough%20jobs%20for%20all%20of%20us%3F%E2%80%9D%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20help%20that%2C%20so%20far%2C%20the%20growth%20of%20renewable%20energy%20is%20concentrated%20in%20some%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Frenewables-integration-in-india%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esouthern%20and%20western%20states%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Shivpal%20Bhagat%2C%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20Oraon%20community%20and%20is%20the%20sarpanch%20of%20Kosampali%20village%2C%20Raigarh%2C%20tells%20us%20that%20his%20family%20has%20lived%20in%20the%20area%20for%20four%20generations%20but%20they%20have%20never%20known%20such%20financial%20insecurity%20before.%20He%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20been%20floundering%20since%20we%20gave%20up%20our%20land%20in%202007.%20We%20were%20expecting%20development%20and%20thought%20we%20would%20get%20stable%20employment.%20Instead%2C%20only%20a%20few%20of%20us%20get%20jobs%2C%20that%20too%20of%20lower%20grades%2C%20and%20with%20contractors.%E2%80%9D%20His%20brother%20Kuldeep%20Bhagat%20pitches%20in%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20our%20parents%20sold%20the%20land%2C%20they%20were%20not%20equipped%20with%20the%20necessary%20information%20or%20understanding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fcoal-mining-1-1.jpg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELand%20should%20be%20returned%20to%20the%20indigenous%20people%20or%20the%20farmers%20who%20originally%20owned%20it.%20Picture%20courtesy%3A%20International%20Accountability%20Project%20%2F%20CC%20BY%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20conflicted%20relationship%20with%20coal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20mining%20activity%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergy.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fcoal%2Ffebruary-2024-sees-11-83-jump-in-indias-coal-production-cil-leads-with-8-69-growth%2F108234485%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasing%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20India%20opened%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Fcentre-issues-allocation-orders-to-successful-bidders-of-22-coal-blocks-123060800965_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E22%20new%20coal%20mines%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0between%202015%20and%202022%2C%20and%20has%20another%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eco-business.com%2Fnews%2Findias-growing-informal-coal-workforce-complicates-energy-transition%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBetween%25202015%2520and%25202022%252C%2520India%2Cworld%252C%252078%2520are%2520in%2520India.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E93%20proposed%20coal%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20the%20other%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1016936%2Fin-indias-coal-belts-jobs-are-now-hard-to-get-and-harder-to-keep%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployment%20in%20the%20coal%20sector%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20not%20seen%20growth.%20The%20use%20of%20mechanisation%2C%20private%20contractors%2C%20and%20mine%20development%20operators%20(MDOs)%20has%20resulted%20in%20fewer%20and%20more%20informal%20engagements.%20By%20some%20estimates%2C%20the%20number%20of%20contractual%20and%20informal%20workers%20in%20the%20sector%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fchrome-extension%2F%2Fefaidnbmnnnibpcajpcglclefindmkaj%2Fhttps%3A%2Fiforest.global%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2FInformal-workers-in-coal-regions-in-India_final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2.4%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20of%20formal%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20residents%20allege%20that%20contractors%20and%20MDOs%20prefer%20people%20from%20other%20states%2C%20often%20their%20own%2C%20for%20most%20of%20the%20work.%20Migrants%20are%20put%20up%20in%20camps%20inside%20the%20mines%20and%20work%20daily%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20they%20add.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20believe%20we%20take%20too%20many%20leave%20days%20and%20prefer%20the%20migrants%20who%20are%20available%20at%20all%20times%2C%E2%80%9D%20alleges%20a%20local%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20locals%20working%20in%20the%20coal%20sector%20seem%20to%20have%20a%20conflicted%20relationship%20with%20it.%20Two%20men%20from%20Churchu%20in%20Hazaribagh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20say%20they%20are%20grateful%20for%20the%20jobs%20they%20secured%20as%20compensation%20for%20their%20ancestral%20land.%20However%2C%20requesting%20anonymity%2C%20both%20allege%20they%20get%20their%20payslips%20from%20different%20companies%20every%20couple%20of%20months.%20They%20are%20confused%20about%20who%20they%20are%20employed%20with%20and%20wonder%20what%20the%20terms%20will%20be%20if%20they%20are%20laid%20off%20and%20whether%20they%20will%20be%20compensated.%20In%20Sarasmal%20village%2C%20a%20guard%20now%20hired%20by%20a%20contractor%20reports%20that%20he%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20his%20cleaning%20job%20with%20the%20mining%20company%20as%20one%20of%20his%20eyes%20was%20deemed%20weak%20after%20a%20medical%20examination.%20In%20Tapranga%2C%20Raigarh%2C%20union%20leaders%20for%20local%20employees%20tell%20us%20they%20would%20be%20devastated%20to%20lose%20their%20jobs%20but%20complain%20about%20how%20houses%20crack%20or%20break%20because%20the%20mine%20is%20too%20close%20to%20their%20colony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bhujangkachar%2C%20located%20on%20the%20precipice%20of%20a%20mine%20in%20Korba%20district%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Bhagwan%20Das*%20who%20lost%20his%20agricultural%20land%20to%20mining%2C%20is%20worried%20that%20the%20excavation%20is%20now%20moving%20closer%20to%20his%20house.%20His%20son%20Shyam%20Das%2C*%20who%20lives%20with%20him%2C%20has%20a%20contractual%20job%20with%20the%20very%20company%20about%20to%20take%20over%20the%20land%20where%20his%20house%20stands.%20Many%20of%20his%20peers%20live%20with%20this%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fno-other-work-villagers-cling-to-coal-despite-damaged-farms-and-homes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eambiguity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Ransahi%20Sonpakat%2C%20says%20he%20prefers%20to%20hedge%20his%20bets%20for%20the%20future.%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20like%20to%20continue%20farming%20the%20land%20I%20have%20remaining%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20not%20as%20much%20as%20before.%20My%20children%20may%20get%20a%20job.%20If%20not%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20have%20land%20so%20they%20can%20use%20it%20for%20agriculture%20later%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20with%20cracks%20in%20its%20walls_coal%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FA-house-with-cracks-from-mining-blasts_resized.jpg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHouses%20crack%20or%20break%20because%20the%20mine%20is%20too%20close%20to%20the%20colony.%20%7C%20Picture%20courtesy%3A%20Debojit%20Dutta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20land%2C%20no%20food%20security%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproximately%2042%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20in%20Jharkhand%20and%20about%2029%20percent%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niti.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2021-11%2FNational_MPI_India-11242021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultidimensionally%20poor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20locals%20equate%20land%20ownership%20with%20food%20security.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20always%20had%20food%20when%20we%20had%20our%20own%20land.%20Now%20we%20need%20to%20pay%20for%20everything.%20The%20salary%20is%20not%20adequate%20for%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ram%20Sewak%20Badal%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20a%20rehabilitation%20colony%20in%20Dhenga%2C%20Jharkhand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Sarasmal%2C%20Bhagwati%20Bhagat%2C%2060%2C%20says%20she%20used%20to%20run%20her%20house%20on%C2%A0%3Cem%3Emahua%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3Etendu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20other%20forest%20pickings.%20%E2%80%9CI%20worked%20for%20six%20months%20and%20that%20was%20enough%20to%20feed%20my%20family%20for%20the%20whole%20year.%20There%20is%20such%20little%20forest%20produce%20now.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20to%20get%20to%20the%20forest%2C%20I%20walk%20across%20the%20mine.%20It%20is%20steep%20and%20dangerous.%20We%20used%20to%20eat%20so%20much%C2%A0%3Cem%3Emoringa%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(drumstick)%20earlier.%20Now%20it%20is%20covered%20in%20soot%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20wash%20it%20many%20times%20before%20we%20can%20cook%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Local%20women%20who%20worked%20as%20agricultural%20labour%20or%20made%20a%20livelihood%20from%20forest%20produce%20are%20deeply%20affected%20by%20coal-related%20displacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mahuatand%2C%20many%20migrate%20to%20other%20regions%20and%20states%20for%20sustenance.%20Others%2C%20however%2C%20succumb%20to%20the%20informal%20coal-gathering%20economy.%20A%20queue%20of%20women%20and%20adolescents%20climb%20down%20a%20precarious%20dirt%20path%20into%20the%20valley%2C%20mobiles%20in%20their%20hand%20so%20they%20can%20use%20them%20as%20torches.%20People%20with%20a%20smaller%20build%20fare%20better%20in%20the%20dark%20underground%20mine.%20The%20company%20has%20made%20a%20trench%20around%20the%20abandoned%20mine%20to%20prevent%20them%20from%20going%20in.%20But%20the%20coal%20gatherers%20have%20broken%20a%20passage%20through%20it.%20Ram%20Manjhi*%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20collect%20and%20sell%20this%20coal%2C%20we%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20cook%20dinner.%20If%20the%20coal%20is%20carried%20out%20in%20trucks%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20development.%20But%20if%20we%20carry%20it%20out%20on%20our%20bicycles%20and%20motorcycles%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20stealing.%E2%80%9D%20One%20of%20the%20many%20people%20displaced%20by%20mining%2C%20Manjhi%20received%20neither%20compensation%20nor%20a%20job.%20After%20he%20vacated%20his%20house%2C%20he%20moved%20closer%20to%20the%20forest.%20He%20alleges%20forest%20officials%20filed%20a%20case%20against%20him%20for%20encroachment%20on%20forest%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bicycle%20carrying%20coal_coal%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FA-bicycle-carrying-coal_resized.jpg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELocals%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20coal%20industry%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sustained%20for%20long%20and%20that%20they%20may%20lose%20their%20land%20for%20nothing.%20%7C%20Picture%20courtesy%3A%20Debojit%20Dutta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELand%20is%20critical%20for%20survival%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERural%20communities%20currently%20facing%20land%20acquisition%20by%20newer%20mining%20projects%20have%20learned%20from%20the%20history%20of%20%E2%80%98coal%E2%80%99%20villages.%20In%20villages%20such%20as%20Jugra%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20and%20Pelma%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20locals%20persistently%20protest%20displacement.%20Chunnulal%20Soren%2C%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ektaparishadindia.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEkta%20Parishad%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0activist%20from%20Vishnugarh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20says%20locals%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20coal%20industry%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sustained%20for%20long%20and%20that%20they%20may%20lose%20their%20land%20for%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESudhlal%20Saw%20is%20a%20sugarcane%20farmer%20in%20Jugra%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20and%20his%20family%20of%20two%20sons%2C%20daughters-in-law%2C%20and%20grandchildren%20work%20together%20to%20produce%20jaggery.%20He%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20refuse%20to%20convert%20my%20generational%20wealth%20to%20money.%20It%20will%20turn%20us%20from%20masters%20of%20our%20land%20to%20servants%20elsewhere.%20Look%20at%20what%20is%20happening%20all%20around.%20Will%20they%20give%20jobs%20to%20all%20of%20us%20for%20every%20generation%3F%E2%80%9D%20Kailash%20Saw%2C%20an%20activist%20in%20the%20village%2C%20points%20out%20the%20folly%20in%20using%20fertile%20land%20for%20excavations.%20%E2%80%9CBarkagaon%20(the%20village%20he%20lives%20in)%20is%20part%20of%20what%20is%20known%20as%20the%20rice%20bowl%20of%20the%20region.%20Why%20are%20we%20using%20this%20land%20for%20mining%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamdular%20Saw%2C%20a%20schoolteacher%20in%20Jugra%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20they%20acquiring%20land%20now%20if%20they%20have%20to%20close%20down%20the%20mine%20in%20three%20or%20four%20decades%3F%20History%20has%20taught%20us%20not%20to%20give%20up%20our%20land%20for%20short-term%20gains.%E2%80%9D%20In%202018%2C%20the%20residents%20of%20Jugra%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FNTPC-land-acquisition-houses-villagers-demolished-jharkhand-jugra%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplained%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20district%20administration%20that%20land%20was%20being%20acquired%20forcefully%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20locals%20have%20been%20protesting%20industrial%20mining%20with%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Farticle%2Frights%2Fcoal-satyagraha-adivasis-reclaim-their-natural-resources%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoal%20satyagraha%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0since%202011.%20In%20Pelma%2C%20Chhatisgarh%2C%20there%20is%20a%20near%20consensus%20that%20mining%20won%E2%80%99t%20change%20their%20fortunes%20for%20the%20better%20but%20for%20the%20worse.%20Rajbala*%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Pelma%2C%20believes%20it%20will%20be%20disastrous%20to%20give%20up%20her%20land.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20will%20be%20a%20big%20loss.%20I%20want%20my%20children%20to%20stay%20here%20and%20continue%20with%20agriculture.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShivpal%20Bhagat%20speaks%20for%20most%20people%20affected%20by%20mining%20in%20the%20region%20when%20he%20says%20that%20jobs%20in%20future%20industries%20will%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20secure%20their%20sustenance.%20%E2%80%9CAgricultural%20land%20is%20critical%20to%20our%20survival%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20Shivpal%20was%20among%20the%20petitioners%20who%20sought%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frights%2Fnational-green-tribunal-jindal-power-coal-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%20damages%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20a%20mining%20company%20for%20failing%20to%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20remedy%20the%20topsoil%20they%20had%20destroyed.%20He%20says%20that%20mining%20companies%20should%20follow%20the%20law%20and%20level%20the%20land%20when%20they%20are%20done%2C%20restoring%20the%20topsoil%20so%20it%20can%20be%20reused%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20local%20communities.%20Union%20leaders%20at%20Tapranga%20say%20that%20even%20infertile%20land%20will%20help%20as%20locals%20can%20use%20it%20for%20fishery%2C%20animal%20husbandry%2C%20and%20other%20livelihood%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20India%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F10%2Findia-needs-legal-framework-for-closing-mines-and-power-plants%2Fhttps%3A%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F10%2Findia-needs-legal-framework-for-closing-mines-and-power-plants%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elacks%20the%20legal%20framework%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0necessary%20to%20facilitate%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Farticle%2Fclimate-emergency%2Fcan-india-undo-its-unjust-transition-from-coal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransfer%20of%20land%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0back%20to%20the%20communities.%20Ramesh%20Sharma%2C%20national%20coordinator%20at%20Ekta%20Parishad%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20government%20has%20taken%20the%20land%20for%20mining%2C%20it%20can%20transfer%20this%20land%20to%20another%20project%20or%20lease%20it%20to%20a%20private%20company.%20Even%20if%20renewable%20energy%20grows%2C%20private%20companies%20will%20get%20large%20tracts%20of%20land%20to%20run%20solar%20or%20wind%20farms.%20But%20land%20should%20be%20returned%20to%20the%20indigenous%20people%20or%20the%20farmers%20who%20originally%20owned%20it.%20It%20can%20be%20co-owned%20by%20communities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproximately%20120%20districts%20in%20the%20country%20have%20sizeable%20fossil-fuel%20or%20related%20industries%20and%20they%20have%20one-fourth%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20population.%20For%20a%20just%20transition%2C%20India%20may%20need%20to%20consider%20a%20strategy%20appropriate%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20affected%20locals%2C%20and%20these%20needs%20are%20rooted%20in%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*%3Cem%3ENames%20changed%20to%20maintain%20confidentiality%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Farticle%2Frights%2Fwhy-coal-communities-are-more-worried-about-land-than-jobs%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2F%5C%22%3EIndia%20Development%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710924351000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20135859%2Fcoal-mining-1-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-coal-communities-are-more-worried-about-land-than-jobs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rural%20communities%20currently%20facing%20land%20acquisition%20by%20newer%20mining%20projects%20have%20learned%20from%20the%20history%20of%20%E2%80%98coal%E2%80%99%20villages.%20Locals%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20coal%20industry%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sustained%20for%20long%20and%20that%20they%20may%20lose%20their%20land%20for%20nothing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-coal-communities-are-more-worried-about-land-than-jobs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222%20Californians%20are%20suing%20Herm%C3%A8s%2C%20saying%20they%20couldn't%20buy%20Birkin%20bags%20even%20after%20one%20of%20them%20spent%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20on%20the%20brand%22%2C%