-chief%2Farticleshow%2F108638749.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraines-survival-in-danger-pentagon-chief%2Famp_articleshow%2F108638749.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraines-survival-in-danger-pentagon-chief%2Famp_articleshow%2F108638749.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20Has%20Failed%20Where%20Nehru%20Had%20Succeeded%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20115055%2FUntitled-design-14.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20elections%20approach%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20strides%20across%20the%20political%20arena%20as%20if%20unchallenged.%20No%20other%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20exuded%20such%20brimming%20confidence%20in%20their%20public%20appearances%2C%20though%20some%20may%20believe%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20came%20quite%20close.%20Nehru%2C%20despite%20the%20adulation%20of%20his%20compatriots%2C%20mostly%20appeared%20weighed%20down%20by%20the%20responsibilities%20he%20had%20assumed%20and%20the%20restraint%20he%20had%20imposed%20upon%20his%20deportment.%20The%20understatedness%2C%20however%2C%20concealed%C2%A0%20a%20gameplan.%20This%20was%20to%20quicken%20India%E2%80%99s%20moribund%20economy%2C%20an%20aspect%20missed%20by%20most%20of%20his%20biographers%20who%20have%20invariably%20devoted%20much%20of%20their%20attention%20to%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20ambitions%20and%20internal%20political%20preoccupations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActually%2C%20in%20their%20focus%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20share%20a%20common%20factor.%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20speech%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20on%20August%2014%20had%20declared%20that%20the%20goal%20of%20independence%20was%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbuild%20up%E2%80%9D%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprosperous%E2%80%9D%20country.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20did%20express%20caution%20in%20assuming%20that%20this%20was%20assured.%20Modi%2C%20ever%20confident%20of%20his%20capabilities%2C%20has%20tended%20to%20be%20more%20emphatic.%20He%20launched%20his%20election%20campaign%20of%202014%20with%20the%20unambiguous%20promise%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CAchche%20din%20aanewale%20hai%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E.%20For%20the%20majority%20in%20India%2C%20better%20days%20can%20only%20mean%20economic%20betterment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20effect%2C%20both%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20emphasised%20the%20importance%20of%20economic%20growth%2C%20and%20staked%20their%20political%20career%20on%20the%20progress%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%E2%80%99s%20position%20is%20revealed%20in%20the%20following%20statement%20he%20made%20in%20parliament%20in%20May%201956%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20whole%20philosophy%20is%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20every%20possible%20way%20of%20growth%20and%20not%20to%20do%20something%20which%20suits%20some%20doctrinaire%20theory%20or%20imagine%20we%20have%20grown%20because%20we%20have%20satisfied%20some%20text-book%20maxim%20of%20a%20hundred%20years%20ago.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%2C%20who%20prefers%20his%20delivery%20upfront%2C%20considered%20the%20maxim%20%E2%80%9Cminimum%20government%2C%20maximum%20governance%E2%80%9D%20sufficient.%20It%20is%20interesting%20to%20spot%20a%20character%20similarity%20between%20these%20two%20otherwise%20ideologically%20opposed%20politicians.%20Firstly%2C%20they%20did%20not%20shy%20way%20from%20declaring%20publicly%20what%20they%20intended%20to%20deliver%2C%20and%20gave%20the%20people%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20they%20would%20achieve%20it.%20This%20is%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20behaviour%20of%20most%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20politicians%20today.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20really%20know%20what%20they%20stand%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20do%20the%20records%20of%20these%20two%20powerful%20prime%20ministers%20of%20India%20stack%20up%20with%20respect%20to%20economic%20growth%3F%20The%20recent%20announcement%20by%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Office%20of%20an%20advance%20estimate%20of%20GDP%20in%202023-24%20gives%20us%20data%20for%20the%20full%20decade%20for%20which%20Modi%20has%20been%20prime%20minister.%20This%20yields%20a%20definite%20picture.%20Far%20from%20having%20accelerated%20after%202014%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%20has%20slowed%20since%202016.%20This%20need%20not%C2%A0%20surprise.%202016%20was%20the%20year%20of%20the%20demonetisation.%20Though%20only%C2%A0%20a%20temporary%20shock%2C%20as%20the%20money%C2%A0%20supply%20returned%20to%20its%20earlier%20level%20quite%20quickly%2C%20the%20shortage%20of%20currency%20could%20have%20triggered%20forces%20making%20for%20slower%20growth%20which%20feed-off%20of%20one%20another.%20The%20economy%20slowed%20for%20three%20successive%20years%2C%20and%20in%202020-21%20it%20actually%20contracted.%20Not%20even%20the%20high%20growth%20rates%20post%20Covid%20have%20been%20sufficient%20to%20negate%20the%20impact%20of%20four%20years%20of%20progressively%20slowing%20growth.%20Everything%20points%20to%20the%20role%20of%20demonetisation%20in%20this%20as%20none%20of%20the%20exogenous%20drivers%20of%20growth%2C%20namely%20world%20demand%2C%20agricultural%C2%A0%20growth%20or%20public%20investment%20slowed%20at%20the%20time.%20Whatever%20may%20be%20the%20reason%2C%20we%20now%20know%20that%20the%20economic%20policies%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%20have%20not%20delivered%20faster%20growth%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20picture%20with%20respect%20to%20economic%20growth%20in%20what%20may%20be%20termed%20the%20Nehru%20era%2C%20lasting%20till%20his%20death%20in%201964%2C%20is%20stark.%20With%20the%20implementation%20of%20policies%20to%20revive%20the%20economy%2C%20gathered%20under%20the%20rubric%20%E2%80%98planning%E2%80%99%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20growth%20rate%20accelerated%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20fifties%20and%20remained%20steady%20till%201964.%20In%20the%20annals%20of%20twentieth%20century%20growth%20the%20Nehru%20era%20was%20pathbreaking.%20While%20we%20have%20reliable%20data%20only%20for%20the%20last%20fifty%20years%20of%20the%20Raj%2C%20we%20know%20that%20the%20colonial%20era%20was%20a%20time%20of%20stagnant%2C%20if%20not%20declining%2C%20per%20capita%20income.%20This%20trend%20was%20decisively%20reversed%20in%20the%20fifties.%20Per%20capita%20income%20has%20not%20stagnated%20since%20then%2C%20though%20growth%20faltered%20for%20about%20a%20decade%20and%C2%A0%20a%20half%20after%20the%20passing%20of%20Nehru.%20The%20transition%20in%20the%20fifties%20to%20a%20permanently%20higher%20growth%20path%20may%20be%20regarded%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98mother-of-all%E2%80%99%20economic%20transitions%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20recorded%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20accounts%20for%20this%20differential%20record%20of%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20with%20respect%20to%20economic%20growth%3F%20Above%20all%2C%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20Indian%20economic%20policy%20was%20guided%20by%20a%20definite%20strategy.%20This%20was%20to%20to%20try%20and%20energise%20an%20economy%20trapped%20at%20a%20low%20level%20of%20income%20via%20a%20big%20push%20to%20be%20provided%20through%20rising%20public%20investment.%20The%20reliance%20on%20public%20investment%20was%20entirely%20for%20practical%20reasons.%20It%20was%20believed%20that%20the%20private%20sector%20was%20unlikely%20to%20come%20up%20with%20the%20level%20of%20investment%20required%20to%20shock%20the%20economy%20into%20motion%20due%20to%20the%20long%20gestation%20period%20and%20high%20uncertainty%20involved.%20This%20strategy%20paid-off%20handsomely.%20As%20the%20Indian%20state%20invested%2C%20so%20did%20the%20private%20sector.%20Most%20would%20be%20surprised%20to%20know%20that%20during%20the%20Nehru%20era%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20private%20sector%E2%80%99s%20investment%20exceeded%20that%20of%20the%20public%20sector%3Cstrong%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20the%20context%2C%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0t%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehis%20should%20not%20surprise%20anyone%2C%20for%2C%20as%20public%20investment%20increases%20it%20generates%20demand%2C%20thus%20expanding%20the%20market%20to%20be%20had%20by%20the%20private%20sector.%20It%20is%20this%20mechanism%20that%20explains%20the%20ending%20of%20what%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20period%20of%20about%20two%20centuries%20of%20stagnation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%20succeeded%20where%20Modi%20failed%20because%20he%20had%20a%20strategy%20for%20growth.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20advisors%20seemed%20to%20have%20encouraged%20him%20to%20think%20in%20terms%20of%20slogans%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cminimum%20government%E2%80%9D%2C%20for%20instance.%20The%20trouble%20is%20that%20the%20pursuit%20of%20minimum%20government%20can%20result%20in%20less%20of%20both%20public%20and%20private%20investment%2C%20as%20can%20be%20seen%20from%20the%20mechanism%20by%20which%20growth%20was%20achieved%20in%20the%201950s%20in%20India.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20private%20investment%20rate%20in%20India%20has%20barely%20budged%20since%202014%2C%20despite%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20avowedly%20business-friendly%20government.%20Having%20finally%20sensed%20the%20folly%20of%20being%20ideologically%20committed%20against%20a%20public%20presence%20in%20the%20economy.%20his%20government%20has%20used%20the%20last%20two%20budgets%20to%20unleash%20a%20blitzkrieg%20of%20infrastructure%20building%20before%20the%20ending%20of%20its%20term%20this%20coming%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20is%20to%20even%20remotely%20suggest%20that%20the%20policies%20of%20the%20Nehru%20era%20were%20ideal.%20First%2C%20exports%20were%20ignored%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20there%20was%20no%20way%20of%20funding%20even%20the%20intermediate%20inputs%20and%20capital%20goods%20needed%20for%20the%20industrialisation%20drive%2C%20leave%20alone%20the%20defence%20equipment%20and%20crude%20oil.%20This%20showed%20up%20in%20the%20balance%20of%20payments%20crises%20that%20had%20plagued%20India%20in%20the%20fifties%20and%20sixties.%20Secondly%2C%20there%20was%20the%20momentous%20neglect%20of%20primary%20education%2C%20especially%20for%20women%2C%20which%C2%A0%20slowed%20the%20adoption%20of%20technology%20and%20better%20practices%20more%20generally%2C%20in%20every%20sphere%20of%20life.%20Human%20development%20would%20not%20only%20have%20led%20to%20a%20much%20faster%20eradication%20of%20poverty%20in%20India%2C%20it%20was%20the%20very%20promise%20of%20Indian%20independence.%20Perhaps%20the%20planners%20imagined%20that%20it%20would%20come%20along%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20growth.%20It%20did%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20as%20if%20growth%20should%20be%20the%20sole%20economic%20indicator%20we%20ought%20to%20be%20concerned%20with%20but%20it%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20history%20that%20both%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20chose%20to%20locate%20it%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20their%20economic%20policy.%20This%20makes%20it%20a%20criterion%20by%C2%A0%20which%20we%20may%20evaluate%20the%20difference%20they%20made%20to%20the%20economy%20in%20their%20time%20as%20prime%20ministers%20of%20India.%20Nehru%20quickened%20the%20economy%20in%20his%20time.%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20is%20yet%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPulapre%20Balakrishnan%20is%20an%20economist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710916245000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20115055%2FUntitled-design-14.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-has-failed-where-nehru-had-succeeded%22%2C%2